text: Sphaenorhynchus botocudo is a frog. It lives in Brazil. The adult male frog is 23.9-29.3 mm long from nose to rear end. It has a black line from the nose to each eye. It has a white spot under each eye. It has a white stripe with brown color around it from each eye to the middle of the body. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Sphaenorhynchus botocudo
